7
00:00:28,230 --> 00:00:33,400
   

8
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:41,980


9
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,640
It's you.

10
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,860
You're the person I feel sincerely about.

11
00:01:14,230 --> 00:01:18,100
   

12
00:01:18,830 --> 00:01:20,360
Oh...

13
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:22,810
Oh...

14
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,410
Oh, no.

15
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:30,250
Sorry. I really had no idea.

16
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:33,630
It's really annoying of me to say that I didn't know,

17
00:01:34,410 --> 00:01:36,330
but I'm really sorry.

18
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:42,120
I didn't say that to make you feel bad.

19
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:48,570
I think I was too comfortable with you and didn't pick up the hints.

20
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:52,510
Don't be uncomfortable, though.

21
00:01:53,860 --> 00:01:55,580
Is that a difficult thing to ask for?

22
00:02:00,890 --> 00:02:02,880
Don't feel sorry,

23
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:05,410
and don't feel uncomfortable either.

24
00:02:05,410 --> 00:02:07,660
Please just think about it once.

25
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:11,780
Can you do that?

26
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,070
O-Okay.

27
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,600
I will.

28
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,260
I think your phone is buzzing.

29
00:02:23,260 --> 00:02:25,080
Wh-What?

30
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:34,190
 I can't come today. Sorry. 

31
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,010
Geez.

32
00:03:04,430 --> 00:03:06,850
 Jung Young Joo: Did you get home safe? 

33
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:09,380
 I'm sorry. I didn't mean to pressure you. 

34
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,270
 Goodnight. 

35
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,400
Hey.

36
00:03:46,420 --> 00:03:48,640
Why didn't you come along earlier?

37
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,280
Mr. Lee said you were coming to help.

38
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:53,890
Why would you need me?

39
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:55,610
I'd only get in the way.

40
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:57,010
Hey.

41
00:03:57,010 --> 00:03:59,320
Still, it's your idea.

42
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:03,930
I worked on it with Young Joo and submitted it.

43
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,700
Good.

44
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:10,400
I can go now, right?

45
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,080
Pardon?

46
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,880
Sure.

47
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:27,200
What's up with him?

48
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:32,220
I'm going crazy.

49
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:45,040
 It's you. 

50
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:47,880
 You're the person I feel sincerely about. 

51
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:05,220
 She didn't say that she liked him, did she? 

52
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:06,670
 No way. 

53
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:09,640
 It's only been a few days since she said she likes me. 

54
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,810
 She rejected him, right? 

55
00:05:12,930 --> 00:05:14,560
Geez.

56
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:17,270
Whatever. I'll just not think about it.

57
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,890
What are you doing?

58
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:21,650
- Do you need help? 
 - What?

59
00:05:21,650 --> 00:05:25,130
Oh, it's nothing. I'm almost done.

60
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,390
Grandpa.

61
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:39,670
Where did you get this cutting board?

62
00:05:40,330 --> 00:05:43,890
Ji Won made it and gave it to me.

63
00:05:58,010 --> 00:05:59,750
Good work.

64
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:01,840
Have this.

65
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,660
Is it already tangerine season?

66
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:05,080
When did you buy them?

67
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:10,030
Well, Ji Won brought a bag full earlier.

68
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:15,740
Oh, this is also from Ji Won.

69
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,970
Did you lend her some clothes?

70
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:21,450
Ki Joon,

71
00:06:21,450 --> 00:06:24,830
can you pass me that back scratcher over there?

72
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:32,710
Oh, this?

73
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:35,920
Ji Won made this for me too.

74
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,730
Ki Joon...

75
00:06:41,730 --> 00:06:44,850
They're selecting a new head of security at my apartment complex.

76
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,920
Should I apply* ? 
  (TN: "Apply" in Korean is pronounced "ji won") 

77
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,370
Stop.

78
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:50,020
Stop, Grandpa. Stop!

79
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:51,980
- Stop. 
 - I shouldn't?

80
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:53,750
From now on,

81
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:56,680
I'm banning the word "ji won" in our house.

82
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,980
It's banned.

83
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:00,020
"Ji Won" is banned.

84
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,490
Hey.

85
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:04,630
What's up with you?

86
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,680
Shouldn't I apply?

87
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,900
You should "try," Grandpa, not "apply."

88
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:16,730
Good work today.

89
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:19,060
- Bye now. 
 - Where should we go?

90
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,020
Let's go.

91
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:22,510
Good work today.

92
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,480
Hyungnim!

93
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,980
Hey.

94
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:32,260
   

95
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:36,550
So aren't you working in this field anymore?

96
00:07:36,550 --> 00:07:38,380
Does teaching suit you?

97
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:41,540
Seriously, who cares if it suits me.

98
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:43,820
I'm just doing it.

99
00:07:45,410 --> 00:07:46,840
All right.

100
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:58,300
Hyungnim, by any chance,

101
00:07:58,330 --> 00:08:01,910
did Sang Rim reach out to you?

102
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:04,480
- Sang Rim? 
 - Yes.

103
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:09,610
I quit working there

104
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:11,630
not long after you left, Chief Lee.

105
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:13,680
They haven't contacted me since then.

106
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,030
Why?

107
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:19,400
Recently... I met Cheol Joo.

108
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,260
Do you remember him?

109
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:24,010
He was injured when he was an apprentice.

110
00:08:24,590 --> 00:08:26,700
Of course, I remember.

111
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:29,810
That accident was why I quit.

112
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:31,470
Was it?

113
00:08:31,470 --> 00:08:35,150
That jerk, the on-site manager, put so much pressure on me.

114
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:37,990
The high-altitude maintenance lift that Cheol Joo was on,

115
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:40,940
It wasn't in good shape so no one wanted to get on it.

116
00:08:40,940 --> 00:08:43,410
After Cheol Joo fell,

117
00:08:43,410 --> 00:08:47,270
they were worried we might testify against them,

118
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:50,250
and they threw a crazy fit.

119
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:52,010
Geez.

120
00:08:52,010 --> 00:08:55,470
I'm not one to lie.

121
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:59,280
And I couldn't really take Cheol Joo's side, so I quit.

122
00:09:00,430 --> 00:09:04,940
I was blacklisted then and now I can't do any work with Sang Rim.

123
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:09,500
Sang Rim has the most constructions around here.

124
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,550
Cheol Joo...

125
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,950
is in a wheelchair,

126
00:09:21,780 --> 00:09:25,520
and his trial with Sang Rim is still ongoing.

127
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:31,020
So what are you going to do? Step forward?

128
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:35,170
I don't really know, to be honest.

129
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:38,180
Where I work happens to be a Sang Rim foundation school.

130
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:42,670
Really. Why are things so complicated?

131
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:48,790
There isn't any evidence or anything that can help, is there?

132
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:52,160
I think the company got rid of the report I submitted.

133
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,780
Gosh. Of course, they did.

134
00:10:03,930 --> 00:10:05,430
You remember back then,

135
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:09,710
the supervisor was slow and frustrating at his work,

136
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:12,190
so you sent texts to the manager directly.

137
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:17,140
Did you send him anything about the high-altitude work?

138
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,430
I did.

139
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:24,100
I think I did.

140
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,290
They should be on my old phone.

141
00:10:26,290 --> 00:10:29,200
Then you can check that.

142
00:10:29,810 --> 00:10:33,340
But my old phone...

143
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:41,100
 - Thank you, goodbye. 
 - Bye. 

144
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:48,480
 Go inside. 

145
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:53,090
 It's my wife! 

146
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:54,940
 Honey. 

147
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:56,750
 Look. 

148
00:10:56,750 --> 00:11:01,780
 I've been calling people at my company and on-site all day, 

149
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:06,070
 but no one is picking up. 

150
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:12,220
 Oh, right. I should call Deputy Jo's wife. 

151
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,710
 Just stop it. 

152
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:24,280
 Stop what? 

153
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:27,440
 They're saying I was bribed. 

154
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,480
 But these people... 

155
00:11:31,370 --> 00:11:33,480
 they all know that I wasn't. 

156
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,870
 They know, so why— 

157
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:37,000
 That's why I said not to get involved. 

158
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,890
 It's not like I did anything wrong. 

159
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:43,510
 I only did it because those people asked me to help them. So— 

160
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:46,890
 Why am I the one getting fired? 

161
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:48,480
 When did I accept a bribe? 

162
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,610
 Minding other people's business can be a sin. 

163
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:53,160
 It's a sin to pretend to be the hero 

164
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:56,160
 and pretend you have skills when you don't. 

165
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,320
 Is that everything you have to say? 

166
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:15,330
 Please pick up. 

167
00:12:16,850 --> 00:12:20,780
 Someone just say something, you— 

168
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:34,570
The old phone?

169
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:38,960
The one you threw and broke?

170
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:43,500
Yes. What did we do after I threw it? Did we just throw it away?

171
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,110
I'm not sure.

172
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:46,910
Why?

173
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:49,140
I caught up with Man Soo,

174
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:52,670
and I remembered sending texts to Manager Gu Byeong Chul.

175
00:12:52,670 --> 00:12:54,600
I think I said that the lift Cheol Joo was on

176
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,620
when he had the accident needed to be exchanged.

177
00:12:57,620 --> 00:13:00,230
Is this because of Cheol Joo's trial?

178
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,990
No, I was just wondering.

179
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:11,510
Do you even know how you got a job at our school?

180
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:14,050
What do you mean?

181
00:13:14,050 --> 00:13:16,730
The person who was here before you,

182
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:18,520
Mr. Kim Moo Kyung,

183
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:21,130
was Cheol Joo's homeroom teacher when he had the accident.

184
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:23,710
He did a lot to take Cheol Joo's side.

185
00:13:23,710 --> 00:13:26,240
- Really? 
 - And now you're here,

186
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,110
but he's gone.

187
00:13:31,070 --> 00:13:33,260
Do you mean that he was fired?

188
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:35,510
- For taking Cheol Joo's side? 
 - I—

189
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:39,460
I don't want to be a bad person to you again.

190
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:43,430
I hope you can keep the promise you made when we divorced.

191
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:46,440
You said you'd be happy solely as Ah Reum's dad.

192
00:13:47,690 --> 00:13:49,740
Mom!

193
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,100
Ji Won.

194
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,380
What?

195
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:28,170
Didn't you bring an umbrella?

196
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:29,630
No.

197
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,360
Thanks.

198
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:39,060
I'll just walk with you to the classroom.

199
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:40,730
Let's go.

200
00:14:40,730 --> 00:14:43,360
Why didn't you bring an umbrella when it's pouring like this?

201
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,080
I know, right?

202
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:48,510
Why is it suddenly raining so much?

203
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:52,990
It has to stop soon, right?

204
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:54,850
Thank you so much.

205
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:12,450
Why do you always only focus on the here and now?

206
00:15:14,430 --> 00:15:16,360
What?

207
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,860
Check on the weather and pack your umbrella.

208
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:21,800
Can't you even do things like that?

209
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,940
Why are you picking a fight? It's only morning.

210
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:32,020
What's this?

211
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:34,090
Try to be prepared.

212
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:39,900
   

213
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:42,250
Don't be a burden to others.

214
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:58,160
 What's he doing? He's confusing me. 

215
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:05,690
Let's go, Eun Bi.

216
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,970
I have no appetite.

217
00:16:15,690 --> 00:16:18,110
Come on. You still have to eat.

218
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:20,810
Eat well and get your strength. Then we can go somewhere better.

219
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:22,220
Here.

220
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:35,800
- What are you doing? 
 - You don't eat carrots.

221
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,810
I'll take the peas out too.

222
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,890
What is it?

223
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,450
Did you see me grab a piece of meat, too?

224
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,010
What?

225
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:04,070
See? You look much prettier when you smile.

226
00:17:04,070 --> 00:17:05,560
Eat up.

227
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:11,770
All right, Eun Bi, I took out all the carrots.

228
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,860
Enjoy your lunch.

229
00:17:18,390 --> 00:17:20,080
Hold on.

230
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,820
Here. This is dessert. 
    

231
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,860
What's up with the bubblegum?

232
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:28,580
Thank you.

233
00:17:30,670 --> 00:17:31,670
Hey.

234
00:17:31,670 --> 00:17:34,780
 And now, today's last story and song request. 

235
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:40,090
 It's been a while since 12th-grader Choi Tae Kang in the Machinery Department sent a story. 

236
00:17:40,090 --> 00:17:43,680
 "Seo Young, I want to be your boyfriend."  

237
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,310
 "I'm so hungry for your love." 

238
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:49,980
 And he requested "Boy in Luv" by BTS. 

239
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:53,110
 Then with Choi Tae Kang's song request, 

240
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,490
 we end the lunch broadcast today. 

241
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:58,070
 I hope you power through the afternoon classes. 

242
00:17:58,070 --> 00:18:00,420
 I'm Kwon Hye Mi broadcasting at NJBS, Nulji, 

243
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:03,670
 reaching everyone across the globe. 

244
00:18:17,050 --> 00:18:18,890
What are you doing?

245
00:18:21,990 --> 00:18:23,670
It's a surprise event.

246
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,140
Seo Young...

247
00:18:30,030 --> 00:18:32,010
Please consider me.

248
00:18:32,010 --> 00:18:34,250
I heard you broke up with that guy.

249
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:35,700
Well?

250
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:37,560
I said, "No."

251
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,840
Seo Young.

252
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,830
What's this?

253
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:48,020
She said "No."

254
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:49,620
What are you to her?

255
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,560
I heard things were over between you two.

256
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:54,470
Right, Seo Young? You ended things with him, didn't you?

257
00:18:58,110 --> 00:18:59,620
Move.

258
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:06,540
This is your last warning.

259
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,070
Stop it.

260
00:19:08,070 --> 00:19:09,630
Got it?

261
00:19:14,490 --> 00:19:15,950
Hey!

262
00:19:15,950 --> 00:19:17,930
Why do you keep talking down to me?

263
00:19:17,930 --> 00:19:19,550
Why?

264
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,250
Kang Seo Young!

265
00:19:24,390 --> 00:19:26,070
What?

266
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:28,100
Are you okay?

267
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:30,480
Yes. I'm fine.

268
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:34,270
You don't have to step in from now on.

269
00:19:34,270 --> 00:19:36,190
Don't worry about it.

270
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:51,000
Young Joo still seems to care about Seo Young.

271
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,100
I don't think Kang Seo Young cares about him at all, though.

272
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:56,490
Why does he keep pining for Kang Seo Young?

273
00:19:56,490 --> 00:19:57,950
He's a fool.

274
00:19:57,950 --> 00:19:59,390
Poor Young Joo.

275
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:01,750
We should treat him nicely in the club.

276
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:03,210
What?

277
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:05,100
