406
00:31:08,450 --> 00:31:10,960
I wrote it so it's mine.

407
00:31:11,900 --> 00:31:14,320
- What about the one I wrote? 
 - As for that...

408
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:16,650
you were going to give it to me anyway.

409
00:31:17,540 --> 00:31:19,160
Wow.

410
00:31:19,950 --> 00:31:21,630
That's impossible logic.

411
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:25,680
So why didn't you give it to me in time so I knew?

412
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:29,830
Whatever. It's all a dark past.

413
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:32,220
I'll deal with it by myself.

414
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:34,520
- I'm going. 
 - Wait—

415
00:31:38,100 --> 00:31:39,970
Well...

416
00:31:39,970 --> 00:31:41,890
Everything's good with you, right?

417
00:31:42,750 --> 00:31:44,070
What?

418
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:48,240
I just meant... Is everything okay?

419
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:52,130
You always go back and forth around this time of the year.

420
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:54,520
"This time of the year"?

421
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,920
You say you like me.

422
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,940
Then you hit me.

423
00:31:59,530 --> 00:32:01,930
Then you say it was a joke.

424
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,350
What are you talking about?

425
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:07,980
Why would you bring that up now?

426
00:32:07,980 --> 00:32:10,100
What I mean is...

427
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:12,220
you know...

428
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:13,710
like...

429
00:32:13,710 --> 00:32:15,410
I was just wondering...

430
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:18,580
if you were suddenly meeting someone, or dating him,

431
00:32:18,580 --> 00:32:21,480
- or something like that. 
 - Hey.

432
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:24,280
What's been up with you since this morning?

433
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:26,750
Stop getting on my nerves.

434
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:29,580
Things are already complicated enough for me.

435
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:39,270
They're complicated for me too.

436
00:32:40,430 --> 00:32:42,190
Geez.

437
00:32:51,260 --> 00:32:53,320
What? Say that again.

438
00:32:58,830 --> 00:33:00,190
Who?

439
00:33:00,190 --> 00:33:02,260
A teacher at our school?

440
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:05,890
Lee Kang Hoon?

441
00:33:18,690 --> 00:33:22,030
I'll deal with the teacher.

442
00:33:23,420 --> 00:33:26,320
So you just focus on wrapping up the trial.

443
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:31,380
If by any chance we lose... it won't just end with you losing your job.

444
00:33:31,380 --> 00:33:35,170
I could be in danger too. Got it?

445
00:33:48,030 --> 00:33:51,700
Teaching Director, I need to see you in my office.

446
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:04,290
Mr. Lee Kang Hoon.

447
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,570
Here you are.

448
00:34:08,330 --> 00:34:09,920
What is it?

449
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:13,070
You weren't picking up your phone.

450
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:16,470
Can we talk for a moment?

451
00:34:16,470 --> 00:34:17,890
Of course.

452
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,680
Keep working.

453
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:34,160
So that boy, Jung Young Joo, is the team leader of this club?

454
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:40,000
Yes, is that a problem?

455
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,350
- Are you close to him? 
 - Sorry?

456
00:34:42,350 --> 00:34:48,390
It seems you're busy taking care of those brothers.

457
00:34:49,990 --> 00:34:52,130
What do you mean?

458
00:34:52,130 --> 00:34:53,990
His older brother,

459
00:34:53,990 --> 00:34:57,420
Jung Cheol Joo. He's a graduate of our school.

460
00:34:57,420 --> 00:35:00,550
I hear you've been meeting with a lot of people

461
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:03,380
for that man's trial.

462
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:05,730
 Hyungnim! 

463
00:35:06,650 --> 00:35:08,170
 Hey. 

464
00:35:12,540 --> 00:35:16,410
So are you planning to testify at the trial or something?

465
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:22,490
All right. Listen carefully.

466
00:35:22,490 --> 00:35:26,340
Cheol Joo's accident has already been defined as an industrial accident.

467
00:35:26,340 --> 00:35:29,210
He already got it all but for some reason,

468
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:32,850
he's nagging at the company, asking for more money.

469
00:35:32,850 --> 00:35:35,600
Well, he's not nagging. I heard

470
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,530
it's about compensation for damages.

471
00:35:37,530 --> 00:35:41,860
That's not all. Jung Young Joo even threw a flowerpot on the director's car

472
00:35:41,860 --> 00:35:44,500
because his brother wasn't getting more money.

473
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:49,350
Director Gu knows all that, but she let it slide.

474
00:35:57,850 --> 00:36:00,990
Let's act properly.

475
00:36:00,990 --> 00:36:04,540
You should stay longer here as a teacher.

476
00:36:04,540 --> 00:36:07,020
I'm sure you can't go back to your old job.

477
00:36:07,020 --> 00:36:08,570
Isn't that right?

478
00:36:08,570 --> 00:36:12,680
Who would hire someone who was fired for receiving bribes?

479
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:15,320
Be grateful to the school

480
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:19,620
and don't repay kindness with a load of crap. Understand?

481
00:36:31,100 --> 00:36:33,380
That was tough.

482
00:36:33,380 --> 00:36:37,680
Still, it's fun to work on it together with friends.

483
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:40,880
Jae Hee, you only made one today.

484
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:45,380
I'm just a perfectionist. I was just being meticulous.

485
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:46,830
Is that right?

486
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:49,530
Great. How admirable.

487
00:36:50,070 --> 00:36:52,400
Hey, Ji Won.

488
00:36:58,930 --> 00:37:01,010
Do you have a second?

489
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:04,700
Pardon?

490
00:37:04,700 --> 00:37:06,980
S-Sure.

491
00:37:07,940 --> 00:37:10,360
We need to talk.

492
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:13,980
What's going on? What secret are you guys sharing?

493
00:37:13,980 --> 00:37:16,250
My gosh. Never mind.

494
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:18,820
We'll get going first. See you tomorrow.

495
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:45,000
What is it? Did you have something to say to me?

496
00:37:46,690 --> 00:37:49,350
I have a lot to say to you.

497
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:51,840
Did you work some more on the stool?

498
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:53,450
I don't have work tomorrow.

499
00:37:53,450 --> 00:37:55,970
Should we meet up in the afternoon and work on it together?

500
00:37:56,940 --> 00:37:59,220
I haven't even started.

501
00:38:00,190 --> 00:38:02,930
I'm so out of it these days.

502
00:38:02,930 --> 00:38:07,380
Have I added to the reasons that you're so out of it?

503
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,560
Ji Won...

504
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:18,950
Have you thought about what I said?

505
00:38:22,850 --> 00:38:25,080
No, I haven't.

506
00:38:26,780 --> 00:38:28,250
I see.

507
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:35,120
Hey.

508
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:39,470
May I be honest with you?

509
00:38:40,610 --> 00:38:42,780
It's a bit intimidating.

510
00:38:45,570 --> 00:38:47,960
There's someone that I like.

511
00:38:48,830 --> 00:38:51,190
I confessed to him recently.

512
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:55,600
I didn't think he cared about me,

513
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,810
so I was going to give up.

514
00:38:58,450 --> 00:39:00,350
But I'm not doing that well with it.

515
00:39:01,290 --> 00:39:02,740
So that's why...

516
00:39:02,740 --> 00:39:06,830
I haven't had time to think about what you said.

517
00:39:06,830 --> 00:39:08,470
I'm sorry.

518
00:39:11,610 --> 00:39:13,490
You're in the same situation as I am.

519
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:18,500
So... Do you regret it?

520
00:39:19,170 --> 00:39:21,530
Do you wish you hadn't confessed?

521
00:39:23,910 --> 00:39:25,790
No.

522
00:39:27,630 --> 00:39:29,430
Me, neither.

523
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:35,400
However it turns out, I don't regret telling you how I feel.

524
00:39:36,060 --> 00:39:40,100
So you shouldn't regret it either.

525
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:42,340
Just do what your heart wants.

526
00:39:47,170 --> 00:39:48,830
Let's go.

527
00:39:48,830 --> 00:39:50,290
Sure.

528
00:40:18,780 --> 00:40:20,740
 I think... 

529
00:40:20,740 --> 00:40:23,700
 I like you. 

530
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:26,790
 It's you. 

531
00:40:26,790 --> 00:40:29,540
 You're the person I feel sincerely about. 

532
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:32,630
 Hey, Ji Won. 

533
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,110
 Do you have a second? 

534
00:40:37,110 --> 00:40:39,180
 We need to talk. 

535
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:57,110
What is she doing this late?

536
00:40:58,850 --> 00:41:00,390
Geez.

537
00:41:02,810 --> 00:41:04,470
Hey!

538
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:09,380
You surprised me. What?

539
00:41:09,380 --> 00:41:10,970
You...

540
00:41:12,910 --> 00:41:15,670
Don't slam the door.

541
00:41:16,470 --> 00:41:18,530
It just slammed.

542
00:41:21,450 --> 00:41:23,360
What was that about?

543
00:41:58,510 --> 00:42:00,240
Oh, Ki Joon.

544
00:42:00,240 --> 00:42:02,510
- Hello. 
 - Are you going to school?

545
00:42:02,510 --> 00:42:05,310
- Yes. 
 - All right.

546
00:42:05,310 --> 00:42:07,360
Ah, Ki Joon.

547
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:11,670
Is something going on with Ji Won at school, by any chance?

548
00:42:12,300 --> 00:42:14,530
- Sorry? 
 - She usually sleeps in,

549
00:42:14,530 --> 00:42:18,280
but she keeps going to school early in the morning lately.

550
00:42:20,590 --> 00:42:22,550
Well, I'm not sure.

551
00:42:22,550 --> 00:42:24,740
Are you guys...

552
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,830
still not being friendly with each other?

553
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:33,220
Get along with each other. You both live under the same roof.

554
00:42:33,220 --> 00:42:34,620
